<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="156" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="47.[675,1210,759,994]" pageId="47" pageNumber="156">
DIAGNOSIS. — Shells small (H to 
<quantity box="[1006,1079,760,783]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="47" pageNumber="156" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
), subcircular, moderately inflated to subspheroidal. Sculpture of radial ribs crossed by commarginal lamellae, that are often fluted. Lunule heart-shaped, often deeply impressed. Hinge plate thick, 2 cardinal teeth and single anterior and posterior lateral teeth in each valve. Ligament external, short. Anterior adductor scar short, slightly detached from pallial line. Ventral margin crenulate.
</paragraph>
